from azure.identity import DefaultAzureCredential

credential = DefaultAzureCredential()
token = credential.get_token("https://vault.usgovcloudapi.net/.default")
print("Auth successful, token acquired")
```

This just gets a token for the Key Vault scope — doesn't touch Key Vault at all, but proves the managed identity or service principal auth is working. If that succeeds, then try the `list_properties_of_secrets()` call to confirm the PE path works end to end.

